    • Constructor Detail

      • RadarEvent

        public RadarEvent(java.lang.String id,
                  java.util.Date createdAt,
                  java.util.Date actualCreatedAt,
                  boolean live,
                  RadarEvent.RadarEventType type,
                  RadarGeofence geofence,
                  RadarPlace place,
                  RadarRegion region,
                  RadarPlace[] alternatePlaces,
                  RadarPlace verifiedPlace,
                  RadarEvent.RadarEventVerification verification,
                  RadarEvent.RadarEventConfidence confidence,
                  float duration,
                  android.location.Location location)

        Represents a change in user state. For more information, see https://radar.io/documentation.

        Parameters:
        id - The Radar ID of the event.
        createdAt - The datetime when the event occurred on the device.
        actualCreatedAt - The datetime when the event was created on the server.
        live - A boolean indicating whether the event was generated with your live API key.
        type - The type of the event.
        geofence - The geofence for which the event was generated. May be null for non-geofence events.
        place - The place for which the event was generated. May be null for non-place events.
        region - The region for which the event was generated. May be null for non-region events.
        alternatePlaces - For place entry events, alternate place candidates. May be null for non-place events.
        verifiedPlace - For accepted place entry events, the verified place. May be null for non-place events or unverified events.
        verification - The verification of the event.
        confidence - The confidence level of the event.
        duration - The duration between entry and exit events, in minutes, for exit events. 0 for entry events.
        location - The location of the event.
        See Also:
        https://radar.io/documentation
